## Enumerations

### enum  {#a552221db0b212c6317a281d5b1526ea1}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="enum llvm::MCSubtargetInfo::HwModeType ">
HwMode IDs are stored and accessed in a bit set format, enabling users to efficiently retrieve specific IDs, such as the <a href="/docs/api/structs/reginfo">RegInfo</a> HwMode <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/callingconv/#abdf8cf606905c10634e831390981b0ed">ID</a>, from the set as required.

<EnumerationListItem name="HwMode_Default">

</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a552221db0b212c6317a281d5b1526ea1a68071036fce39ffb8575399199660c02" />
<EnumerationListItem name="HwMode_ValueType">

</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a552221db0b212c6317a281d5b1526ea1a764f5038bd82e3a7058768002532e596" />
<EnumerationListItem name="HwMode_RegInfo">

</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a552221db0b212c6317a281d5b1526ea1a910a78a6661e7f860a0a44fa232feecf" />
<EnumerationListItem name="HwMode_EncodingInfo">

</EnumerationListItem>

</EnumerationList>

Using this approach, various types of HwMode IDs can be added to a subtarget to manage different attributes within that subtarget, significantly enhancing the scalability and usability of HwMode. Moreover, to ensure compatibility, this method also supports controlling multiple attributes with a single HwMode <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/callingconv/#abdf8cf606905c10634e831390981b0ed">ID</a>, just as was done previously.
